<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751>
    bibo:endPage "101" ;
    bibo:journal "ZooKeys" ;
    bibo:startPage "85" ;
    bibo:volume "965" ;
    dc:creator "Nguyen, Dinh Tao; Ho, Anh Tuan; Hoang, Ngoc Thao; Wu, Hua; Zhang, E" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "' Henicorhynchus' thaitui, a new species of cavefish from Central Vietnam (Teleostei, Cyprinidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure2>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure3>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure4>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure5>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure6>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure7> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Lateral view of ' Henicorhynchus' thaitui sp. nov.: a IEBR 105901, holotype, 74.3 mm SL; and b IHB 2016105898, paratype, 98.0 mm SL. Both specimens caught in central Vietnam: Son River system in Gianh river drainage: Khe Lanh Cave." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/449263" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. ' Henicorhynchus' thaitui sp. nov., specimen not preserved, about 100 mm SL, Vietnam: Khe Lanh cave; life coloration." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/449264" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. ' Henicorhynchus' thaitui sp. nov., IHB 2016105898, paratype, 98.0 mm SL: a lateral view of head b gill rakers on lower arm of first arch c pharyngeal teeth d air bladder; and e intestines." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/449265" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Ventral view of mouthpart structures in ' Henicorhynchus' thaitui sp. nov., IHB 2016105898, paratype, 98.0 mm SL. lj, lower jaw; ll, lower lip; mb, maxillary barbel; pg, postlabial groove; rb, rostral barbel; rf, rostral fold; ul, upper lip; uj, upper jaw." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/449266" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Species most closely related to ' Henicorhynchus' thaitui sp. nov.: a Henicorhynchus lineatus b H. lobatus c H. ornatipinnis d H. siamensis e Cirrhinus jullieni f C. microlepis g C. molitorella; and h Speolabeo hokhanhi. Photos b, d, e, f and g from Vietnam, by D. D. Tran (Can Tho University, Vietnam); a and c from Laos, by Bounthob Praxaysombath (National University of Laos, Laos) (from Kano et al. 2013); and h from Vietnam, by D. T. Nguyen. Scale bars: 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/449267" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Map showing the distribution of ' Henicorhynchus' thaitui sp. nov. (▲)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/449268" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.965.52751.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Vietnam: Son River system in Gianh River drainage basin: Khe Lanh Cave: mouth of cave (left) and habitat of ' Henicorhynchus' thaitui sp. nov. (right)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/449269" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

